  "response_text": "A busy, slightly comic office scene opens on a dark-haired, middle-aged man seated behind an overflowing desk. He wears a white shirt, dark vest, and tie, and his workspace is packed with papers, trays, notebooks, wires, rods, and odd homemade communication devices. A green banker-style hanging lamp glows above him. Around him are metal tubes and horn-shaped speaking devices, including a large flared horn over his left shoulder and several mechanical arms stretching across the desk. He has more than one telephone receiver crowded around his head and neck, and he looks harried as he tries to manage calls and signals at once.\n\nHe sits forward with one receiver to his ear, then reaches across the desk toward the right, where a colorful panel of buttons, cords, and levers sits among the clutter. He grabs a yellow handset-like object, speaks into or toward it, then drops it back down. Still wearing receivers around his neck and against his ear, he turns toward a wall of devices beside a window. He points and gestures as if trying to direct a message through the improvised setup. Frustration builds visually: he raises both hands, then reaches up toward the metal speaking horn above him, as though calling through it.\n\nThe view shifts to another office worker at a separate crowded desk. This man is fair-haired, wears glasses, a white shirt, suspenders, and a dark bow tie. He sits under a metal desk lamp, surrounded by stacks of paper, trays, pencils, and another flared speaking horn aimed at him from the left. As he reacts to the incoming message, loose sheets lift and flutter, and his hair is blown straight upward, making him look startled and overwhelmed. He looks toward the horn, then down at the papers in his hands, trying to cope with the disorderly system.\n\nBack at the first man’s desk, the dark-haired man continues with a black phone receiver pressed to one ear and another white receiver hanging around his neck. He raises the brass-colored h